This paper deals with a facility location problem, which involves finding the optimal location of facilities to cover a set of points. This problem is commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of non-decreasing functions and optimization also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem may also involve game theory (cs.GT) if there are multiple agents involved in the facility location. Finally, the use of Lp metric suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
